299
00:16:25,181 --> 00:16:26,981
It's Masked Yaiba!

300
00:16:26,981 --> 00:16:29,081
I'm using the same color

301
00:16:29,081 --> 00:16:31,281
for the masked Yaiba that I'm making now too.

302
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:33,581
So, the finish is...

303
00:16:33,581 --> 00:16:35,281
Yes, no mistake about it.

304
00:16:35,281 --> 00:16:36,781
It's the same color.

305
00:16:36,781 --> 00:16:39,781
I see. So, that's the story.

306
00:16:40,981 --> 00:16:42,781
You're all still here?

307
00:16:42,781 --> 00:16:44,681
Hurry on home.

308
00:16:46,181 --> 00:16:48,881
Like I said, Dr. Agasa.

309
00:16:48,881 --> 00:16:52,781
What is this, gathering everybody here like this?

310
00:16:52,781 --> 00:16:55,881
I'm sorry. I know it's really sudden but...

311
00:16:55,881 --> 00:16:59,081
There are several things that keep bothering me

312
00:16:59,081 --> 00:17:01,081
as to the crime that occurred.

313
00:17:01,081 --> 00:17:03,781
First of all, it's Reika's broche

314
00:17:03,781 --> 00:17:06,481
that was found on the floor of the corridor.

315
00:17:06,481 --> 00:17:09,981
Mr. Kitajima's blood was found on the broche.

316
00:17:09,981 --> 00:17:12,881
But, please take a good look at her clothes.

317
00:17:12,881 --> 00:17:15,481
There is no blood on it at all.

318
00:17:15,481 --> 00:17:17,681
Do you think it's possible

319
00:17:17,681 --> 00:17:22,081
that splattered blood would pinpoint just the broche?

320
00:17:22,081 --> 00:17:25,981
Then, are you saying that someone left

321
00:17:25,981 --> 00:17:28,981
the broche with blood stain on it to frame her?

322
00:17:28,981 --> 00:17:30,681
But, that's no very likely.

323
00:17:30,681 --> 00:17:34,681
And there's another strange thing.

324
00:17:34,681 --> 00:17:37,781
Mr. Morishita, it's about you.

325
00:17:37,781 --> 00:17:39,381
Me?

326
00:17:39,381 --> 00:17:43,081
Yes, when I first met you.

327
00:17:43,081 --> 00:17:45,081
This is the most popular robot anime around now.

328
00:17:45,081 --> 00:17:48,881
You explained that you were working all night making a piece,

329
00:17:48,881 --> 00:17:50,981
and your clothes were soiled with paint.

330
00:17:50,981 --> 00:17:52,881
Yes, the one you're wearing.

331
00:17:52,881 --> 00:17:54,381
However...

332
00:17:59,181 --> 00:18:02,281
Please take a look at that robot.

333
00:18:02,281 --> 00:18:04,681
It's what Mr. Morishita made.

334
00:18:04,681 --> 00:18:06,381
The colors are vivid.

335
00:18:06,381 --> 00:18:09,281
The colors are completely different from the color on his clothes.

336
00:18:09,281 --> 00:18:11,081
Why is that?

337
00:18:11,081 --> 00:18:13,981
Inside Mr. Morishita's paint case

338
00:18:13,981 --> 00:18:17,581
there was paint the same color as the stain on his clothes.

339
00:18:17,581 --> 00:18:19,381
It's this!

340
00:18:19,381 --> 00:18:22,781
This color is for some reason

341
00:18:22,781 --> 00:18:26,781
the same as the color used for Mr. Kitajima's georama.

342
00:18:26,781 --> 00:18:32,281
There were rumors going around that Mr. Kitajima had a ghost modeler.

343
00:18:32,281 --> 00:18:37,681
Mr. Morishita, isn't it you who was ghost modeling for him?

344
00:18:37,681 --> 00:18:38,981
That's right.

345
00:18:38,981 --> 00:18:40,981
